Deputy National Security Advisor for Cyber and Emerging Technology Anne Neuberger and Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs Victoria Nuland briefed ambassadors and representatives from 35 countries on the Counter-Ransomware Initiative (CRI) and U.S. government efforts to combat ransomware. Under Secretary Nuland discussed the Department of State's strategies, including using foreign assistance to enhance partner capacity against threats and establishing a new Bureau of Cyberspace and Digital Policy. She also encouraged countries to utilize existing international frameworks such as the Budapest Cybercrime Convention and the UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime. Deputy National Security Advisor Neuberger provided updates on the outcomes of the CRI meeting held on October 13-14, where participants recognized the importance of integrating law enforcement, cybersecurity, financial regulators, and foreign affairs ministries. The United States is collaborating with CRI partners to identify areas for future cooperation, including improving network resilience, addressing ransom laundering in virtual currencies, supporting ransomware-related investigations and prosecutions, and enhancing diplomatic cooperation.